               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420228-name-1402" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1402" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1402" type="surname" value="PARKINSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1402" type="given" value="WILLIAM CALVERT"></interp>WILLIAM CALVERT PARKINSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a sergeant of the 13th Light Dragoons, and live in Gardener's-lane. I employed the prisoner on the 9th of February, at my lodging, to mend some clothes for me in my room—I missed a ring that day from a trunk in my room, where I had placed it that morning—it was not locked—I charged the prisoner with taking it—he denied it—I told the corporal to fetch a policeman—he called the corporal back, and said he would show where the ring was—it was pro<lb></lb>duced by the policeman—this is it—it is mine, and is worth 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.</p>
